st_remarks: Measurements from a spruce dominated plot. The soil is classified as a boulder-rich, sandy glacial till several meters deep. Dystric Regosols that consist of a thin organic layer a reddish B-horizon and a yellowish-gray C-horizon. Sandy loams containing many stones of all sizes up to 80 cm diameter. Fraction of fine material (<2mm) is only 30%! The stone content increases with depth. Below about 70 cm the soils are very compact with very few roots.The ground water table is highly variable.
